author: cmpilato
msg: Ditch the whole scan-ahead, namespace-mapping complexity in favor of
simplicity:  properties in the "svn" and "custom" namespaces use
prefixes, oddball others use xmlns="" attributes.
"I don't plan to spend much time here," I said.  Heh...
(proppatch_walker): Don't use mapping hashes.  Just use predefined
prefixes for namespaces that have them, and "xmlns=" attributes
(create_proppatch_body): Revert all the dynamic prefix definition
determine the property's name and namespace.
(change_dir_prop, change_file_prop): Don't mess with property maps
to property determine the property's name and namespace.
